<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Magic Downpour</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img style="width: 200px; height: 200px;" title="Magic Downpour" src="/file/Elden-Ring/magic_downpour_sorcery_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="magic downpour sorcery elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Spell Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Carian Sorceries" href="/Carian+Sorceries" target="">Carian Sorceries</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost&nbsp;18</td> 
     <td>Slots Used&nbsp;1</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Summon a magic mass that sprays projectiles over area 
      </div> <br><img style="float: left;" title="Attributes Requirement" src="/file/Elden-Ring/attributes-required-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="attributes required elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">Requires 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;15 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a> 0 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane" target="">Arcane</a>&nbsp;0 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Magic Downpour</strong> is a&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sorceries" href="/Sorceries" target="">Sorcery</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Magic Downpour spell</strong>&nbsp;creates a mass of magic, that deploys projectiles over a large area. Can also be cast while moving. Updated to&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>One of the sorceries of the Carian royal family.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Summons a mass of magic that fires projectiles over a wide area.<br>This sorcery can be cast while in motion. Charging extends<br>duration.<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>Said to have been taught by the Crystalians to mark the swearing<br>of the old concord.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Magic Downpour</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Magic Downpour</strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Preceptor Miriam" href="/Preceptor+Miriam">Preceptor Miriam</a> in the Carian Study Hall. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=6001&amp;lat=-143.41406&amp;lng=81.00479&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=6001&amp;lat=-143.41406&amp;lng=81.00479&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Interactive Map Link</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Magic Downpour Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Carian Sorceries" href="/Carian+Sorceries">Carian Sorcery</a></li> 
 <li>Stamina Cost:&nbsp;17</li> 
 <li>Deals magic damage</li> 
 <li>This spell is boosted by the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Carian Glintblade Staff" href="/Carian+Glintblade+Staff">Carian Glintblade Staff</a></li> 
 <li>Contrary to other similar spells, Magic Downpour actually can be aimed at a specific target when casting, as opposed to targeting a single pre-set area.&nbsp; This makes it particularly useful against large enemies who can be hit repeatedly by the spell.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Charging the spell increases the duration of the spell, allowing you to overlap multiple casts on top of each other to further increase damage.</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff6600;"><em>NOTE:</em></span>&nbsp;Since&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>&nbsp;FP Consumption has been Decreased from 20 to 18.</li> 
</ul> 
